Go to a sepulchre, contemplate dust ashes worms and sigh
Behold how that corpse becomes first yellow, and then black
Afterward the whole body is covered in a white and disgusting mold

In that corruption a multitude of worms is generated, which feed on the flesh

The cheeks, the hair, the lips fall to pieces. The ribs are first laid bare, then the arms and legs.
The worms after having consumed all the flesh devour each other.
And at last nothing remains of that body but a skeleton, which in time crumbles in pieces the bones seperate and the head falls from the trunk
See then what a man is? A little dust on the barnfloor which is carried away by the wind.
In this picture of death behold yourself and what you will one day become. Remember that thou art dust, and to dust thou shalt return
Consider that in a few years, perhaps a few months and day thou becamest rottenous in worms.
